The paper deals with the construction and analysis of nested codes, which are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of algebraic geometry codes and the Hermitian curve also suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and algebraic geometry (cs.AG). Additionally, the paper involves mathematical optimization and analysis, which could fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
